title: High Speed CAN Communication Bus Malfunction
description: This code indicates a general malfunction in the high-speed Controller Area Network (CAN) communication bus, which is critical for many vehicle systems to communicate.
symptoms: Check Engine Light, various other warning lights may illuminate (ABS, transmission, etc.), multiple system malfunctions, engine may not start or run poorly, erratic gauge readings.
causes: Wiring issues in the high-speed CAN bus (open, short, high resistance), faulty ECU(s) connected to the high-speed bus, termination resistor issues, PCM/ECM problem.
solutions: Inspect wiring harness and connectors for damage or corrosion, diagnose individual ECUs connected to the high-speed bus, check termination resistors, diagnose PCM/ECM. This often requires specialized diagnostic equipment.
severity: High - Can cause widespread system failures.
diagnosis: Use a specialized scan tool capable of reading communication bus data. Check for communication with different ECUs on the high-speed bus. Inspect wiring and connectors for the CAN bus. Check termination resistor values.

title: High Speed CAN Communication Bus Performance
description: This code indicates a performance issue with the high-speed CAN communication bus, meaning communication is occurring but not reliably or efficiently.
symptoms: Check Engine Light, intermittent malfunctions in various systems, erratic data readings, communication timeouts.
causes: Wiring issues (high resistance, intermittent connections), electromagnetic interference (EMI), excessive bus load, faulty ECU(s) causing communication errors.
solutions: Inspect wiring and connectors for corrosion or damage, shield wiring from potential EMI sources, diagnose ECUs for communication errors, reduce bus load if possible.
severity: Moderate to High - Can lead to unpredictable system behavior.
diagnosis: Use a communication bus diagnostic tool to monitor bus traffic and signal quality. Check for excessive retries or error frames. Inspect wiring routing and shielding.

title: High Speed CAN Communication Bus (+) Open
description: This code indicates an open circuit in the positive (+) wire of the high-speed CAN communication bus.
symptoms: Check Engine Light, loss of communication with some or all ECUs on the high-speed bus, multiple system malfunctions.
causes: Broken wire in the CAN (+) line, faulty connector.
solutions: Locate and repair the open circuit in the CAN (+) wire, repair or replace faulty connector.
severity: High - Disrupts communication on the bus.
diagnosis: Use a multimeter to check continuity of the CAN (+) wire between different ECUs.

title: High Speed CAN Communication Bus (-) Open
description: This code indicates an open circuit in the negative (-) wire of the high-speed CAN communication bus.
symptoms: Check Engine Light, loss of communication with some or all ECUs on the high-speed bus, multiple system malfunctions.
causes: Broken wire in the CAN (-) line, faulty connector.
solutions: Locate and repair the open circuit in the CAN (-) wire, repair or replace faulty connector.
severity: High - Disrupts communication on the bus.
diagnosis: Use a multimeter to check continuity of the CAN (-) wire between different ECUs.

title: High Speed CAN Communication Bus (+) Short to Ground
description: This code indicates a short circuit between the positive (+) wire of the high-speed CAN communication bus and ground.
symptoms: Check Engine Light, communication errors on the bus, some ECUs may not respond.
causes: Damaged wiring causing a short to ground.
solutions: Locate and repair the short circuit in the CAN (+) wire.
severity: High - Can disrupt communication and potentially damage ECUs.
diagnosis: Use a multimeter to check for a low resistance path between the CAN (+) wire and ground.

title: High Speed CAN Communication Bus (-) Short to Ground
description: This code indicates a short circuit between the negative (-) wire of the high-speed CAN communication bus and ground.
symptoms: Check Engine Light, communication errors on the bus, some ECUs may not respond.
causes: Damaged wiring causing a short to ground.
solutions: Locate and repair the short circuit in the CAN (-) wire.
severity: High - Can disrupt communication and potentially damage ECUs.
diagnosis: Use a multimeter to check for a low resistance path between the CAN (-) wire and ground.

title: High Speed CAN Communication Bus (+) Short to Battery
description: This code indicates a short circuit between the positive (+) wire of the high-speed CAN communication bus and the vehicle's battery voltage.
symptoms: Check Engine Light, communication errors, potential for ECU damage due to overvoltage.
causes: Damaged wiring causing a short to battery voltage.
solutions: Locate and repair the short circuit in the CAN (+) wire.
severity: High - Can cause significant damage to ECUs.
diagnosis: Use a multimeter to check for higher than expected voltage on the CAN (+) wire.

title: High Speed CAN Communication Bus (-) Short to Battery

solutions: Locate and repair the short circuit in the CAN (-) wire.

diagnosis: Use a multimeter to check for higher than expected voltage on the CAN (-) wire.

title: High Speed CAN Communication Bus (+) Short to (-)

solutions: Locate and repair the short circuit between the CAN wires.
severity: High - Disrupts all communication on the bus.
diagnosis: Use a multimeter to check for a low resistance path between the CAN (+) and (-) wires.
